Goodyear Lastikleri TAS (GOODY) , the Turkish
unit of  Goodyear Tire & Rubber Co. (GT) , rose for a third day in
Istanbul after Sabah reported that Turkey will make winter tires
mandatory.  Goodyear climbed 5.4 percent to 58.25 liras at the close in
Istanbul, bringing three-day gains to 8.9 percent.  Turkeyâ€™s traffic safety board decided to make winter tires
mandatory after traffic accidents rose 10 percent in the first
three months of the year from the same period in 2011, Sabah
newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
